A Sustainable Life with @krobin32 of @bythesun_____ ❤️

Co-founder of one of our latest ethical clothing lines, By The Sun, and 2x Olympic Medalist Kelsey Robinson Cook, chats to us about her daily life, sustainable habits and inspiration behind starting By The Sun. Travelling as a professional athlete, Kelsey has had the opportunity to see first hand the negative effects of consumerism which motivated her to think deeply about her personal impact on the planet and how starting a brand like By The Sun was another way to make a positive difference.

Today on International Women's Day, we are grateful to showcase the woman that @krobin32 is on and off the court. You can't summarize an entire person in an Instagram carousel, but we tried! Kelsey Robinson Cook is much more than one of the most talented volleyball players in the world (although she certainly is). Beyond her Olympic gold and silver medals, MVP Awards, and many other prestigious medals and awards, Kelsey is layered, as we all are.

She is creative, she loves freely, and notices the beauty in everything around her. Kelsey is a talented photographer and documents the details as she goes in her photos. Sometimes her hubby @robertsoncook joins in and photographs her. Their photos are not only artful, but showcase scenes from all over the world that they've captured in their travels. Kelsey is an entrepreneur. In November of 2022, she launched her fashion line @bythesun_____. The elevated loungewear is consciously designed, sustainably created, and ethically produced. The clothes reflect Kelsey in their whimsical, effortless and graceful personality.

We are incredibly grateful to have Kelsey in the LOVB family, and we cannot wait to see what the future holds for her as a LOVB Founding Athlete... both on and off the court! ❣️

#LOVBforLife
